<p class="p">The equation yields plane wave free solutions (i.e., with right-hand side of 
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="E1" class="xref">Eq. 1</xref> set to zero)
 <disp-formula id="E2" class="disp-formula">
  <math id="m2" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ψ</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <msup class="msup">
      <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">e</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">i</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">k</mi>
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">x</mi>
       <mo class="mo">+</mo>
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">l</mi>
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">y</mi>
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">ω</mi>
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">t</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </msup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
  <label class="label">(2)</label>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> is the zonal wave number, 
 <italic class="italic">l</italic> is the meridional wave number, ω is the frequency of zonally propagating waves, and 
 <italic class="italic">t</italic> is time.
</p>
